{{More footnotes|date=May 2018}}
The Mark 22 nuclear bomb (Mk-22) was the first thermonuclear device test by the [[University of California Radiation Lab]] (UCRL). The test was part of the [[Castle Koon|''Koon'' shot of Operation Castle]]. The Mk-22 failed to achieve anything like its intended yield due to premature heating of the secondary from exposure to neutrons. As the other UCRL test planned for the Castle series, the liquid fueled "[[Ramrod]]" device had the same basic [[Product defect|design flaw]], that test was canceled. Within a month of the bomb’s failure, the Mk-22 was terminated because the [[United States Atomic Energy Commission]] realized there was nothing that could be done to salvage the design.

